Usage: editMove [-help] {[[-direction {x y diag45 diag135} -distance <float> ] | [-dx <float> -dy <float>] | -to {x y}] }

-help                               # Prints out the command usage
-direction {x y diag45 diag135}     # Specifies the
                                    # direction(x|y|diag45|diag135)
                                    # (enum, optional)
-distance <float>                   # Specifies in microns, the distance to
                                    # move the wire. (float, optional)
-dx <float>                         # Specifies dx move, in microns, the
                                    # distance to move the wire in x direction.
                                    # (float, optional)
-dy <float>                         # Specifies dy move, in microns, the
                                    # distance to move the wire in y direction.
                                    # (float, optional)
-to {x y}                           # Specifies the coordinate of destination,
                                    # in microns. (point, optional)